
Adding Bootstrap:
    - You can add bootstrap to any app by linking your html to: 
        >> <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-BVYiiSIFeK1dGmJRAkycuHAHRg32OmUcww7on3RYdg4Va+PmSTsz/K68vbdEjh4u" crossorigin="anonymous"/>

Sizing Images to fit screens appropriately:
    - Add >> class="img-responsive" to <img></img>

Centering text: 
    - Add class >> class="text-center"

Buttons: 
    - To make a standard button with Bootstrap
        >> <button class="btn btn-default">Like</button>
    - Make button span the page
        >> class="btn-block"
    - Make buttons stand-out 
        >> class="btn-primary"
        >> class="btn-info"
        >> class="btn-danger"

Icons: 
    - Add little icons to your buttons or elsewhere with the i div
        >> <i class="fas fa-thumbs-up"></i>
        >> <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i>
        >> <i class="fas fa-info"></i>
        >> <i class="fas fa-trash"></i>

Boxes: 
    - Bootstrap works alongside the "grid" format, this means you can add classes to divs that will represent the size and positioning you want
        >> class="col-xs-4"
    - Fit multiple elements within a "row" div, giving each their own div of how much room they are to take up